{
  "text": "To clarify that the injected electrons and holes originate from the generated charges in the C 60 /pentacene OSHJ rather than from those injected from the external electrodes (ITO and Al) in our C 60 /pentacene OSHJ-based OLEDs, electron-only ( Figure 2a (Figure 2c and 2d). The extremely low currents in these two devices should be attributed to the large injection and transport barrier between the ITO (,4.7 eV) and electron-transporting organic TPBi (highest occupied molecular orbital (HOMO) ,6.2 eV) [CITATION_1] and C 60 (HOMO ,6.2 eV) [CITATION_2] for holes and between the Al (,4.3 eV) and hole-transporting organic TCTA (lowest unoccupied molecular orbital (LUMO), 2.7 eV) [CITATION_3] and pentacene (LUMO ,3.0 eV) [CITATION_4] . We note that the conventional device shown here is under its optimum structure.",
